                    <h2>Learning support when you need it</h2>
                    <p>SLU takes an innovative approach to learning. Going a step a further than the classroom, beyond the hands-on, and into the experiential with Learning Communities that promote creative and academic support for your degree program. Our 9:1 student-to-faculty ration enhances your education. Study alongside other international students, domestic students, staff and faculty as you dive into exciting research. Or pursue an internship with one of the many start-ups local to St. Louis. Or learn from your favorite professor-turned-mentor as you shape your future at SLU.</p>
<p>Develop your unique network at SLU—the special blend of faculty, advisors, mentors and peers who make up your community of support. You don’t have to look hard to find them. Our community helps you turn experiences into practice, and practice into a professional future. It’s a safe place that helps you find your voice and base it on research and values. A major research institution with $43.2 million invested into research, we support your research and career development. SLU ranks as the #1 Best College for Jobs in Missouri (Zippia 2018).</p>

